Review:
The lead role of Liam Neeson (Oscar Schindler) is the best, of course. Played flawlessly. I would like to believe that he was not the only person who saved the Jews from death.

Some moments in the film are so memorable that it just breaks a tear:
a moment with a pretty girl with curls in a red coat;
the moment when teeth are dismantled for gold;
the moment when everyone is waiting for gas in the soul ...;
how children hide in the bottom of the toilet...
how mothers run after trucks with children;
terrible executions, often insane;


There were many more of these moments, but I remember these. This is a story and this film must be seen to know what it was, and how terrible it was and what these people experienced. How valuable life is and what it is worth ... immediately, your own life is assessed differently.
